  "description": {
    "en-US": "The canonical Office of Corpus Christi composed by Aquinas in 1264 at the request of Pope Urban IV — *Sacerdos in aeternum*, the recension ultimately adopted by the Church. Includes the four great Eucharistic hymns *Pange Lingua*, *Sacris Solemniis*, *Verbum Supernum*, and the sequence *Lauda Sion*. Aquinas Institute bilingual edition.",
    "la": "Officium Corporis Christi canonicum Thomae 1264, Urbano IV petente — recensio *Sacerdos in aeternum*, in usum Ecclesiae tandem recepta. Comprehendit hymnos Eucharisticos maximos *Pange Lingua*, *Sacris Solemniis*, *Verbum Supernum*, et sequentiam *Lauda Sion*."
  },
